Reviews: Wait, what? Yeah. I wrote a one star here a while back. They made a mistake and I've since learned to lighten up when bad stuff happens! Ya gotta cool off a bit before you start! This Weinerschnitzle location has always been my favorite due to the location, staff, and then there's the one of a kind menu! They make their fries to order so you won't be getting limp, lifeless, cool fries. No, you get smokin hot French fries to go with that smokin hot Chilli cheese dog! Five stars, can't miss, I gotta have it once a week!
Replies: Bullet points: - Fries are made to order - Fries are not limp, lifeless or cool - French fries are served hot - French fries pair well with Chilli cheese dog

Reviews: This is the closest Weinerschnitzel location to me. The food is doable on certain days and it's a complete miss on others.  Quality control and quality as a whole is nonexistent so come here at your own risk.  The only item I come here for are the Chili Cheese Fries and my cravings usually aren't satisfied. There is usually at least one issue regarding stale fries, unmelted cheese, and|or the orders are made half a**.  FYI- keep an eye out for coupons in the mail. The food isn't worth paying full price!!
Replies: Bullet points: - Inconsistent food quality. - Chili Cheese Fries are the only satisfying item. - Issues with stale fries and unmelted cheese. - Not worth paying full price.

Reviews: Don't order the pretzel bun dog with cheese. You get a pretzel bun and a side of cheese no dog. Been ordering this for years. First time I've had no dog in it. Went back through the drive thru only to be told we got what we ordered a pretzel bun with cheese. Ummm no I ordered a pretzel bun DOG with cheese. Then opened the cheese only to have plastic in it. Terrible
Replies: Bullet points: - Cheese contained plastic. - Food quality issue.

Reviews: Only good thing bout this place is the milkshakes! Please don't waste your money on the chili cheese fries/burgers/hotdogs, after taste, tastes like it's been placed in dirty water. The fries was not crispy or cooked, the chili tasted watered down, & the cheese was like plastic. Good customer service tho
Replies: Bullet points: - Chili cheese fries/burgers/hotdogs are not recommended - After taste is unpleasant and tastes like it's been placed in dirty water - Fries are not crispy or cooked well - Chili tasted watered down - Cheese is like plastic

Reviews: I am scared to go here again after I watched someone pick up a French fry  from the floor they dropped and put it back in the fryer.  John

Kinda sucks that this is the closest Weinerschnitzel to where i'm currently living at.  I've been coming here on and off for years.  Over the years the pricing has gone up and the quality has gone down.  I used to come here regularly (about 4x / month) and got to know the workers and assistant managers.  It was to the point where they would hook me up with coupon prices even if I didnt have the coupon.     Nowadays, if you dont have a coupon, you're paying full price.  And like the previous Yelper said, the food is not worth paying full price for.
Replies: Bullet points: - Food quality has decreased. - Previous reviewer mentioned that the food is not worth paying full price for.

Reviews: I found two transparent white black larvae floating around my later soda cup filled with lemonade many hours ago. The first one I found was when I filled my second cup at the soda machine, so I dumped it out and refilled it again but when I got to school at around 2:45 PM. I found another thinner transparent white black floating around my lemonade drink so I dumped it out again, please consider having a soda machine repairs man to come by and clean the machine. It can be very hazardous! But overall the food is very good, as always.
Replies: Bullet points: - Food quality is very good.

Reviews: I guess compared to the other reviews I got lucky today. I ordered a corndog, small fries, and Mug rootbeer. Ordering was quick and efficient. The corndog was fresh tasting. The cornbread coating was slightly sweet with distinct corn taste. The hotdog had a slight snap to it as I bit into it. Overall I was pleased with my corndog experience. The fries were awesome. Very hot, and slightly crispy. They were not oily, and reminded me of Micky D's back in the day when they could make killer fries. The rootbeer was cold, crisp, and refreshing. I took this snack to go so I can't really comment on dining in. I was happy with my choices and would choose to do this again.
Replies: Bullet points: - Corndog had fresh taste and distinct cornbread coating - Hotdog had a slight snap - Fries were hot, crispy, and not oily - Rootbeer was cold, crisp, and refreshing

Reviews: I ordered 3 chili fries and drove home 2 find out the fries are stale. I call and they keep hanging up on me. On going 2maro 2see a manager and get my $ back. SMH.
Replies: Bullet points: - Customer ordered 3 chili fries. - Upon arrival home, the fries were found to be stale.

Summary: Based on the bullet points provided, there are both positive and negative reviews about the food quality at Weinerschnitzel. Starting with the positive reviews, customers appreciated the freshness and taste of the corndog and hotdog, as well as the crispiness and hotness of the fries. Some customers also mentioned that the root beer was refreshing. Additionally, many customers liked that the fries were made to order and served hot, and paired well with the chili cheese dog. However, there were also several negative reviews about the food quality. Customers reported inconsistent food quality, with the chili cheese fries being the only satisfying item. There were also issues with stale fries and unmelted cheese. Some customers reported that the cheese contained plastic, and that the food quality was overall disappointing. One customer reported that they found the fries to be stale upon arrival home. In addition to the above, some customers reported that the chili cheese fries/burgers/hotdogs are not recommended, and tasted unpleasant with an aftertaste that tasted like it's been placed in dirty water. They also mentioned that the fries were not crispy or cooked well, and that the chili tasted watered down with cheese that is like plastic.
